FILE: tools.rs
MOD: mcp/tools
ROLE: MCP tool definitions — broker_register, broker_send, broker_presence, broker_peek, broker_messages, broker_send_stanza
EP: BrokerTools::new; broker_register; broker_send; broker_send_stanza; broker_presence; broker_peek; broker_messages
STAB: volatile
INV:
  - broker_send XML-escapes the message parameter before stanza construction (xml_escape fn) — plain text only
  - broker_send_stanza passes raw XML through unescaped — caller is responsible for valid XML
  - All three network tools (broker_peek, broker_messages, send_raw) include X-Agent-Name header
  - SessionManager holds all credential state — BrokerTools is stateless except for the session Arc
  - broker_register handles 409 (project exists) by loading key from disk — graceful re-registration
  - broker_register accepts optional description param — forwarded to /agents/register; omitted defaults to ""
  - broker_presence includes description suffix " — {desc}" when non-empty; omits when blank
  - send_raw is the single HTTP send path — both broker_send and broker_send_stanza route through it
LOOK: xml_escape; send_raw header set; broker_register 409 path
CHK: cargo build -p mcp after changes
CNTR: mcp/tools::broker_send depends_on mcp/session::SessionManager
